  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Deposits LP collateral into the Treasury in exchange for newly-minted LP shares.\\n\\nA deposit consists of:\\n- `pairs_to_deposit` LONG tokens\\n- `pairs_to_deposit` SHORT tokens\\n- `pairs_to_deposit * collateral_per_pair` USDC\\n\\nShares are minted proportional to the deposit's NAV relative to the Treasury's total NAV.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`TreasuryError::InvalidInput`] if `pairs_to_deposit == 0`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ActionPaused`] if deposits are paused.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the number of LP shares minted for the depositor.",
      "name": "deposit",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pair",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pairs_to_deposit",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "u128"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Withdraws LP collateral from the Treasury by burning LP shares.\\n\\nThe caller specifies the number of shares to burn. The Treasury computes the\\nproportional amount of LONG/SHORT/USDC owed, validates safety constraints, and\\ntransfers the tokens to the user.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`TreasuryError::InvalidInput`] if `shares == 0`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ActionPaused`] if withdrawals are paused.\\n- [`TreasuryError::InsufficientShares`] if `shares > user_shares` or `total_shares == 0`.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the token amounts withdrawn: `{ long, short, usdc }`.",
      "name": "withdraw",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pair",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "shares",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
