  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Buys **LONG** tokens from the Treasury using USDC.\\n\\nThe caller supplies `usdc_in` and receives `long_out` quoted from the current\\noracle price and fee model. This trade is executed **against Treasury inventory**:\\nthe Treasury must already hold sufficient LONG to deliver the trade.\\n\\n### Pricing & Fees\\n- Uses `prices.long` from the oracle.\\n- Computes a dynamic taker fee via `calculate_fee(...)`.\\n- `quote_buy_token` returns `(long_out, usdc_fee)`; `usdc_fee` is retained and tracked.\\n\\n### Slippage Protection\\nReverts if `long_out < min_long_out`.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`TreasuryError::InvalidInput`] if `usdc_in == 0`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ActionPaused`] if trading is paused.\\n- [`TreasuryError::Slippage`] if output is zero or below `min_long_out`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::InsufficientInventory`] if the Treasury lacks LONG inventory.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the amount of LONG transferred to the user.",
      "name": "buy_long",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pair",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "usdc_in",
          "type_": "u128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "min_long_out",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "tuple": {
            "value_types": [
              "u128",
              "u128"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Sells **LONG** tokens to the Treasury in exchange for USDC.\\n\\nThe caller supplies `long_in` and receives `usdc_out` quoted from the current\\noracle price and fee model. This trade is executed **against Treasury USDC inventory**:\\nthe Treasury must have sufficient USDC to pay out.\\n\\nAdditional safety checks apply to protect LPs:\\n- LONG-side trades may be blocked as \"toxic\"\\n- USDC floor constraints prevent draining too much collateral in a single trade\\n\\n### Slippage Protection\\nReverts if `usdc_out < min_usdc_out`.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`TreasuryError::InvalidInput`] if `long_in == 0`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ActionPaused`] if trading is paused.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ToxicSideNotAccepted`] if risk logic blocks LONG sells.\\n- [`TreasuryError::Slippage`] if output is zero or below `min_usdc_out`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::InsufficientInventory`] if the Treasury lacks USDC to pay out.\\n- [`TreasuryError::CannotPassFloor`] if paying out violates the USDC floor.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the amount of USDC transferred to the user.",
      "name": "sell_long",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pair",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "long_in",
          "type_": "u128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "min_usdc_out",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "tuple": {
            "value_types": [
              "u128",
              "u128"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Buys **SHORT** tokens from the Treasury using USDC.\\n\\nThe caller supplies `usdc_in` and receives `short_out` quoted from the current\\noracle price and fee model. This trade is executed **against Treasury inventory**:\\nthe Treasury must already hold sufficient SHORT to deliver the trade.\\n\\n### Pricing & Fees\\n- Uses `prices.short` from the oracle.\\n- Computes a dynamic taker fee via `calculate_fee(...)`.\\n- `quote_buy_token` returns `(short_out, usdc_fee)`; `usdc_fee` is retained and tracked.\\n\\n### Slippage Protection\\nReverts if `short_out < min_short_out`.\\n\\n### Reverts\\n- [`TreasuryError::InvalidInput`] if `usdc_in == 0`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::ActionPaused`] if trading is paused.\\n- [`TreasuryError::Slippage`] if output is zero or below `min_short_out`.\\n- [`TreasuryError::InsufficientInventory`] if the Treasury lacks SHORT inventory.\\n\\n### Returns\\nReturns the amount of SHORT transferred to the user.",
      "name": "buy_short",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "pair",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "usdc_in",
          "type_": "u128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "min_short_out",
          "type_": "u128"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "tuple": {
            "value_types": [
              "u128",
              "u128"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
